    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.96/83a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5812. For <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName> from
                    War Trade Board:</p>
                <p>7. Since your departure Swiss have submitted suggested agreement differing in
                    substance as well as form from one worked out by <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_TAE1">Taylor</persName>. We are convinced Swiss
                    agreement should be negotiated and concluded by you and <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_TAE1">Taylor</persName> in Paris in conference
                    with committees there with full knowledge of the situation. Grimprel and
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PLE1">Percy</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d301fn2">Temporarily attached to the French and British
                        Embassies, respectively.</note> coincide with this view. Prompt answer
                    necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
